This paper deals with the problem of predicting crime hotspots using machine learning models in low population density areas. The paper focuses on developing an imbalance-aware hyper-ensemble for spatio-temporal prediction, which is a problem related to classification and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). However, the paper also deals with machine learning models, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also uses socio-economic, geographical, temporal, meteorological, and crime variables, which are related to data science and information theory, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) another possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with sparsity and class imbalance, which are related to computational complexity and algorithms, making cs.CY (Computational Complexity) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with spatio-temporal patterns, which are related to data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another possible sub-category.
